'''Endeavorist''' ({{IPAc-en|ɛ|n|ˈ|d|ɛ|v|ə|r|ɪ|s|t}}) is a science-oriented web application incorporating [[social networking]], [[crowdfunding]], and research collaboration services within a central "curiosity network".<ref>{{cite web|last=Pierre|first=Carl|title=DC Area-Based Endeavorist Launches New Kickstarter to Document the Process of Creating a Startup|url=http://inthecapital.streetwise.co/2012/09/04/dc-area-based-endeavorist-launches-new-kickstarter-to-document-the-process-of-creating-a-startup/|work=In the Capital|accessdate=23 April 2014}}</ref>  The platform is designed to increase public accessibility to scientific endeavors and products thereof. The stated mission of Endeavorist is "to democratize the pursuit of knowledge and drive scientific endeavor through human curiosity."<ref>{{cite web|last=Matthews|first=Tom|title=A Message for the CEO of Endeavorist|url=http://endeavorist.wordpress.com/2014/04/25/a-message-from-the-ceo-of-endeavorist/|work=Endeavorist Company Blog|accessdate=28 April 2014}}</ref>

Endeavorist is currently publicly available as an [[open beta]]. The planned duration of the open beta period is unknown.

==History==
Endeavorist, LLC was founded on April 24, 2012 in [[Fairfax Station]], [[Virginia]], a [[suburb]] in the [[Washington, D.C. metropolitan area]].<ref>{{cite web|first=|title=Endeavorist, LLC Virginia Domestic Limited-liability Company|url=http://www.bizapedia.com/va/ENDEAVORIST-LLC.html|work=Bizapedia|accessdate=23 April 2014}}</ref> The website remained in closed development for over two years before becoming available to the public as an open beta, launched on April 26, 2014, at the [[USA Science and Engineering Festival]].<ref>{{cite web|title=USASEF: 2014 Expo Exhibits|url=http://www.usasciencefestival.org/2014-festival/2014-exhibits.html?format=html&Itemid=490&option=com_content&view=article&id=395&no_page=&flag=&qexhibits=&age=&keyword=&category=&pavilion=22&peek_friday=&no_page=|publisher=USA Science & Engineering Festival|accessdate=28 April 2014}}</ref>

